Probabilistic Methods. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of hidden Markov models (HMMs), which are a type of probabilistic model, for modeling and classifying dynamic behaviors in vision tasks. The paper specifically focuses on coupled HMMs, which provide an efficient way to model interacting processes and offer superior training speeds, model likelihoods, and robustness to initial conditions. The paper does not discuss any other sub-categories of AI.
